==English==
[[File:Tetramorph meteora.jpg|thumb|A cherub, as described by Ezekiel.]]

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|cerubin}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|cherub}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|χερούβ}}, ultimately from {{etyl|he|en}} {{m|he|כרוב|כְּרוּב|tr=kerúv}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|chĕrʹəb}}, {{IPA|/ˈtʃɛɹəb/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|cherubim|cherubims}}

# A winged creature represented over 90 times in the [[Bible]] as attending on God, later seen as the second highest order of [[angels]], ranked above [[throne]]s and below [[seraph]]im. First mention is in [http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Bible_%28World_English%29/Genesis#Chapter_3 Genesis 3:24]
# A statue or other depiction of such a being, typically in the form of a winged child.
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} A person, especially a child, seen as being particularly innocent or angelic.

